FT  16 FEB 94 / International Company News: Mining boost
North Broken Hill Peko, the diversified Australian mining group, is to
accelerate underground mine production at its Northparkes gold and copper
project, which it is developing in conjunction with the Sumitomo group of
companies.
The development will enable process plant production capacity to rise from
45,000 tonnes a year of copper contained in concentrate to 65,000 tonnes.
